Description: SRC-S guitar body made by Rosser Guitars located in North Carolina. 2 piece semi hollow hard white ash with a 2 piece hard white ash drop top. Body has been stained and then painted with polymer spray paints for a satin finish. You can use as is or it would be perfect to relic or refinish. Set for 3 P90 Soap Bar Pickups and a Jazzmaster Type Bridge and Tremolo The body will be routed for a Strat style neck with standard U.S.A. specs. Some adjustments and sanding may be required depending on the neck. Neck mounting holes drilled, tremolo mounting holes will need drilled. Also strap button holes will need drilled. The body is 25.5" scale. Neck pockets is angled to work properly with the bridge. The control cavity for the body is rear routed and pre-drilled for one 3 way toggle switch, one volume and one tone as shown in photo. The body is drilled for a 7/8" jack. Wiring holes are drilled. About 5 and a half pounds. Also including Jack Plate, Stew Mac Wiring kit and Free - Way - 6 Way Toggle Switch Don't have time to assemble so selling. Free Shipping in the Continental US. Normally I can only ship Saturdays This body is a custom made body and not associated with Fender
